class Solution {
    public long[] sumOfThree(long num) {
        long ans[] = new long[3];
        if(num%3==0){
            ans[0]=num/3-1;
            ans[1]=num/3;
            ans[2]=num/3+1;
            return ans;
        }
        long arr[] = {};  
        return arr;
    }
}
/* 
(x-1) + (x) + (x+1) = 3*x

-Also, the number should be divisible by 3.
-If it is, then assign the numbers.
-If it is not, make an empty array and then return it.
-Java automatically, intialise all the elements by 0, so we are not returning array 'ans'.
-We are making a total empty array 'arr' an returning it.
